track.name: Dark Was the Night - Cold Was the Ground
comments: First time I ever heard this, cannot adequately describe how much it moved me, so I won't...[2]
First time I ever heard this, cannot adequately describe how much it moved me, so I won't...
So soulful and sublime. It was a piece for the passion could be applied to anyone’s suffering. Sometimes you just hurt so much that words fail and all that is left is moans.

the inspiration to ry cooder's haunting soundtrack to paris, texas....and he even does a cover of this....all very well done, but this original is just incredible!  i don't have the words for how incredible this song is.....
randomly happened upon this song and artist. So good!!
On repeat from midnight until 4 am is the best way to appreciate this song
He made it to a "hospital',but they would not treat him 'cause he was black.They were blinder than he ever was...

We let this genius die alone in the rain, shivering with fever,  lying on wet newspapers in the ruins of his burned-out house because he had noplace else to go.  Now his music is out there in the cosmos, and that's gorgeous and absolutely _right_--but I'd much rather someone had given him a warm bed and taken him to a doctor.  One can only imagine the music he'd've made later in life.
I'm surprised this doesn't come higher in the Blind Willie listening charts.
